{#- synth_dialogue.j2 -- template version: v1 (keep META_TEMPLATE_VERSION in
    src/sales_agent/data/synthesize.py in sync when editing).

    Renders the user-turn instruction for the strong model to synthesize ONE
    multi-turn energy sales dialogue as a JSON object. All task-specific prompt
    content lives here; build_prompt() prepends a short generator system message
    and wraps this render as the single user message. Variables come from
    SynthTask.prompt_vars (see expand_task_matrix); `examples` is a list of
    pre-serialized JSON seed dialogues for few-shot anchoring. -#}
You are generating synthetic training data for an English-speaking energy sales
voice agent that works for "ABC Energy", a residential and small-business
electricity supplier.

Produce ONE realistic, self-consistent multi-turn sales conversation for this
exact configuration:

- Scenario: {{ scenario }}{% if scenario_hint %} -- {{ scenario_hint }}{% endif %}
- Customer persona: {{ persona }}
{% if objection_type and objection_type != "none" %}- Primary customer objection: {{ objection_type }}
{% endif %}- Desired conversation outcome: {{ outcome }}
- Target length: about {{ n_turns }} assistant turns.
{% if examples %}
Study these example dialogues and match their style, brevity, and JSON format.
Do NOT copy them -- invent a fresh conversation with different specifics:
{% for ex in examples %}
Example {{ loop.index }}:
{{ ex }}
{% endfor %}{% endif %}
Output ONLY a single JSON object, no markdown fences and no commentary, with
exactly this shape:

  {"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "..."},
                {"role": "user", "content": "..."},
                {"role": "assistant", "content": "..."}]}

Hard requirements:
1. messages[0] MUST be a "system" message (one or two sentences) establishing
   the assistant as a professional, compliant ABC Energy sales agent suited to
   this persona.
2. After the system message, strictly alternate "user" (the customer) and
   "assistant" (the agent): start with "user" and end with "assistant". Aim for
   about {{ n_turns }} assistant turns.
3. The assistant MUST NOT invent or quote any specific price, rate, tariff,
   discount figure, or per-unit cost. Forbidden examples: "$0.09", "9 cents per
   kWh", "12 p/kWh", "save $50 a month". When price comes up, the assistant
   gathers usage details and offers to prepare a personalized quote instead of
   stating a number. The customer MAY mention their own bill amounts.
4. Keep every reply short and natural for a phone call (1-3 sentences).
5. English only. Make the dialogue specific to the scenario below.

Scenario guidance: {{ scenario_directive }}
